settingslib
~~~~~~~~~~~

Simple settings wrapper. No 'sections'. Supports settings loading
from objects and .py files. Works with Python 2.4 and higher.


>>> from settingslib import Settings
>>> settings = Settings('settings')  # from module.
>>> settings.A
1
>>> settings.get('SOME_OBJECT')
'somemodule.some_object'
>>> settings.get('SOME_OBJECT', imp=True)
<SomeObject object at 0x...>
>>> settings2 = Settings({'A': 1}, B=2)
>>> settings2['B']
2

>>> settings.update(A=2, B=1)
>>> settings.update({'A': 1, 'B': 2})

